SHEET CLASSIFICATION RULES
Place each row into exactly one sheet. Do not add, create, or output a Category column. Use category/type information only to decide the sheet.

Classification routing:
- MEMORY: Use only for memory-specific monitoring/threshold/reboot/recheck cases. Memory cases remain on MEMORY.
- MACD: Use only for true adds, moves, changes, deletes, decommissions, implementations, or other clear change-order work.
- MAINTENANCE: Use only for true request/maintenance work, not incident cases.
- PROBLEM: Use only for true problem-management cases.
- INCIDENT:
  - Priority 1 or Priority 2 → P1-P2 MOS MCP
  - Priority 3 or Priority 4 → P3-P4 MOS MCP

VOICE INCIDENT ROUTING
Apply this rule only to incident cases. If a row is a true Voice incident, route Priority 2 Voice incidents to P1-P2 MOS MCP; route all other Voice incidents to P3-P4 MOS MCP.
Do not route incident cases to MAINTENANCE merely because the text contains maintenance-like wording. Use MAINTENANCE only for true request/maintenance work, not incidents. Use MACD only for true change-order work. Use MEMORY only for memory-specific monitoring/threshold/reboot/recheck cases; memory cases remain on MEMORY even if they also mention Voice or incident-like wording.
When source category/type evidence exists, use it first. Incident rows remain incident rows unless the source clearly identifies them as MACD, maintenance/request, problem-management, or memory cases.

